OL,7,FHe also admitted making hundreds of
OL,8,Findecent images of children and
OL,9,Fviewing videos of children being
OL,10,Fsexually abused.
OL,12,FA further offence of breach of a
OL,13,Fprevious Sexual Harm Prevention Order,
OL,14,Fwhich barred him from contact with
OL,15,Fchildren under 16, was also admitted
OL,16,Fat Grimsby Crown Court.
OL,18,FDefending Hoodlass, Craig Lowe said
OL,19,Fhis client had been candid about his
OL,20,Foffending. "He realises he has a real
OL,21,Fproblem and needs assistance with it."
