OL,7,FJudge Woolfall said Hoodlass posed "an
OL,8,Fexceptionally high risk to the public"
OL,9,Fand imposed an extended sentence.
OL,11,FHe jailed Hoodlass for a total of 13
OL,12,Fyears and three months, which includes
OL,13,Fa four-year extension because of the
OL,14,Fdanger he poses.
OL,16,FHe said that Hoodlass would be
OL,17,Feligible for parole after half the
OL,18,Fsentence and the rest of the sentence
OL,19,Fwould be on licence.
